{#- Changelog — tabular rendering.

    One row per run; most recent first. The "v" column is a positional RUN
    SEQUENCE number (newest entry = highest vN), NOT the entry's schema-version
    field (which is a constant). Inline delta cells use the `+A / ~C / -R`
    shorthand (added / changed / resolved).

    Delta basis (entry.delta_basis):
      • fingerprint — full run diffed against the PRIOR entry's stored
        fingerprints → real per-finding delta. Detail block lists added
        (linked) + resolved (by prior fingerprint label, no dangling anchor).
      • incremental — baseline-diff computed upstream (git baseline_sha set).
      • count-only — a prior entry exists but predates fingerprinting, so we
        show a snapshot count ("N total") instead of a fake "+N added".
      • initial — first run on this repo.

    Data shape per entry (see schemas/threat-model.output.schema.yaml):
      version, date, mode, baseline_sha, current_sha, delta_basis,
      threat_count, previous_date, previous_threat_count, fingerprints[]
      mitigation_fingerprints[] (builder), abuse_case_fingerprints[] (patched
        in late by render_abuse_cases.py — abuse cases postdate the builder)
      changed_files, changed_lines ({insertions, deletions})
      added:    { threats: [T-NNN,...], mitigations: [M-NNN,...],
                  abuse_cases: [AC-NNN,...], components: [...], attack_surface: [...] }
      changed:  { threats: [T-NNN,...] }
      resolved: { threats: [T-NNN,...], fingerprints: ["comp|cwe|title",...], reason_by_id: {...} }
      reanalyzed_components, carried_forward_components, note

    Inputs:
      - changelog: list of entries (newest first)
      - threats_by_id: dict T-NNN -> title (used to render bullets with titles)
-#}
## Changelog

_Append-only history of assessment runs. Most recent first._

| Version | Date | Mode | Depth | Reasoning | Baseline → Current | Δ Threats | Code | Note |
|---------|------|------|-------|-----------|--------------------|-----------|------|------|
{% for entry in changelog %}
{%- set run_no        = (changelog | length) - loop.index0 -%}
{%- set prior_run     = run_no - 1 -%}
{%- set date          = entry.date or '—' -%}
{%- set mode          = (entry.mode or 'full') | lower -%}
{%- set depth         = (entry.assessment_depth or '—') | lower -%}
{%- set reasoning     = entry.reasoning_model or '—' -%}
{%- set basis         = entry.delta_basis or '' -%}
{%- set baseline_sha  = entry.baseline_sha or '' -%}
{%- set current_sha   = entry.current_sha or '' -%}
{%- set has_baseline  = (baseline_sha | length) > 0 -%}
{%- set short_base    = baseline_sha[:7] -%}
{%- set short_cur     = current_sha[:7] if current_sha else '' -%}
{%- set added_t       = (entry.added.threats   if entry.added   else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set changed_t     = (entry.changed.threats if entry.changed else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set resolved_t    = (entry.resolved.threats if entry.resolved else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set resolved_fp   = (entry.resolved.fingerprints if entry.resolved else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set n_resolved    = (resolved_fp | length) if resolved_fp else (resolved_t | length) -%}
{%- set threat_count  = entry.threat_count | default(added_t | length) -%}
{%- set has_prior     = (entry.previous_date or '') | length > 0 -%}
{%- set changed_files = entry.changed_files | default(none) -%}
{%- set cl            = entry.changed_lines or {} -%}
{%- set ins           = cl.insertions | default(none) -%}
{%- set dels          = cl.deletions | default(none) -%}
{%- set note          = (entry.note or '') | trim -%}
{#- Aggressive truncation — the table row is narrow; long notes wrap the
    whole changelog illegibly. Upstream the orchestrator is instructed to
    keep `note` ≤12 words. -#}
{%- if note|length > 60 -%}{%- set note = note[:58] ~ '…' -%}{%- endif -%}
{%- if note -%}{%- set note = note | replace('|', '\\|') -%}{%- endif -%}
{#- Δ Threats: the +added / ~changed / -resolved delta only when the row
    represents a real diff against a baseline — a git baseline (incremental),
    a fingerprint delta (full over an existing model), or an explicit
    incremental basis. A from-scratch full snapshot (no baseline, everything
    in `added`) shows an honest count instead of a fake "+N added". -#}
{%- set is_delta_row = has_baseline or basis in ['fingerprint', 'incremental'] -%}
{%- if is_delta_row -%}
{%- set delta_cell = '+' ~ (added_t|length) ~ ' / ~' ~ (changed_t|length) ~ ' / -' ~ n_resolved -%}
{%- else -%}
{%- set delta_cell = (threat_count | string) ~ ' total' -%}
{%- endif -%}
{#- Baseline → Current cell. Git baseline (incremental) shows the sha range;
    a full run over an existing model shows "(vs v<prior>)"; a first run shows
    "(initial)". -#}
{%- if has_baseline -%}
{%- set sha_cell = '`' ~ short_base ~ '` → `' ~ short_cur ~ '`' -%}
{%- elif has_prior -%}
{%- set sha_cell = ('`' ~ short_cur ~ '` ' if short_cur else '') ~ '(vs v' ~ prior_run ~ ')' -%}
{%- else -%}
{%- set sha_cell = '_(initial)_' -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- set code_parts = [] -%}
{%- if changed_files is not none and changed_files -%}
{%- set _ = code_parts.append((changed_files|string) ~ ' files') -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- if ins is not none and dels is not none -%}
{%- set _ = code_parts.append('+' ~ ins ~ '/-' ~ dels) -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- set code_cell = code_parts | join(', ') if code_parts else '—' -%}
| v{{ run_no }} | {{ date }} | {{ mode }} | {{ depth }} | {{ reasoning }} | {{ sha_cell }} | {{ delta_cell }} | {{ code_cell }} | {{ note or '—' }} |
{% endfor %}
{#- Detail block for the LATEST entry. Rendered when the latest run has a
    comparable baseline (incremental git diff OR a fingerprint delta) AND there
    is an actual delta to show. Skipped for the initial / count-only run where
    "everything is added" would just restate the Threat Register. -#}
{%- if changelog -%}
{%- set latest = changelog[0] -%}
{%- set latest_run = changelog | length -%}
{%- set la_t   = (latest.added.threats      if latest.added   else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set la_m   = (latest.added.mitigations  if latest.added   else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set la_ac  = (latest.added.abuse_cases  if latest.added   else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set lc_t   = (latest.changed.threats   if latest.changed  else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set lr_t   = (latest.resolved.threats  if latest.resolved else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set lr_fp  = (latest.resolved.fingerprints if latest.resolved else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set latest_basis = latest.delta_basis or '' -%}
{%- set latest_has_baseline = (latest.baseline_sha or '') | length > 0 -%}
{%- set show_detail = latest_has_baseline or latest_basis in ['incremental', 'fingerprint'] -%}
{#- On any iterative run (incremental git-baseline OR full-over-existing
    fingerprint delta) enumerate the actual finding IDs — definitely the new
    ones, and the resolved ones where possible. IDs are linked WITHOUT titles
    (compact, the title lives in §8). Resolved findings are NOT linked: they no
    longer exist in this document, so a `#t-nnn` link would dangle. The block
    renders even with zero delta so an unchanged iterative run is explicit. -#}
{%- if show_detail %}

**Latest run (v{{ latest_run }}) — threat-level delta:**
{% if la_t %}
- **Added ({{ la_t|length }}):** {% for tid in la_t %}[{{ tid }}](#{{ tid|lower }}){{ ", " if not loop.last }}{% endfor %}
{% endif -%}
{% if lc_t %}
- **Changed ({{ lc_t|length }}):** {% for tid in lc_t %}[{{ tid }}](#{{ tid|lower }}){{ ", " if not loop.last }}{% endfor %}
{% endif -%}
{% if lr_t %}
- **Resolved ({{ lr_t|length }}):** {% for tid in lr_t %}{{ tid }}{{ ", " if not loop.last }}{% endfor %} _(removed since the prior run — not linked: no longer in this document)_
{% elif lr_fp %}
- **Resolved ({{ lr_fp|length }}):** {% for fp in lr_fp %}{%- set fpp = fp.split('|') %}{{ (fpp[2] if fpp|length > 2 else fp) | title }}{% if fpp|length > 1 and fpp[1] %} ({{ fpp[1] }}){% endif %}{{ "; " if not loop.last }}{% endfor %} _(identified by fingerprint — T-IDs are not stable across full runs)_
{% endif -%}
{% if la_m %}
- **New mitigations ({{ la_m|length }}):** {% for mid in la_m %}[{{ mid }}](#{{ mid|lower }}){{ ", " if not loop.last }}{% endfor %}
{% endif -%}
{% if la_ac %}
- **New abuse cases ({{ la_ac|length }}):** {% for ac in la_ac %}[{{ ac }}](#{{ ac|lower }}){{ ", " if not loop.last }}{% endfor %}
{% endif -%}
{% if not (la_t or lc_t or lr_t or lr_fp or la_m or la_ac) %}
_No threat-, mitigation-, or abuse-case-level changes since the previous run (v{{ latest_run - 1 }})._
{% endif -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- endif -%}
